18
00:00:03,430 --> 00:00:04,500
Those are yours.

19
00:00:05,340 --> 00:00:07,390
We bought them together.

20
00:00:07,670 --> 00:00:10,430
Because you "Found the pattern soothing."

21
00:00:18,890 --> 00:00:20,490
I'm gonna miss you, Shaun.

22
00:00:21,530 --> 00:00:22,870
I love Carly.

23
00:00:25,080 --> 00:00:26,260
And that's great.

24
00:00:26,550 --> 00:00:28,470
I am so happy for you.

25
00:00:28,590 --> 00:00:32,310
Now you can hang the toilet paper incorrectly

26
00:00:32,310 --> 00:00:33,700
anytime you want.

27
00:00:33,970 --> 00:00:35,220
And Carly and I can go back

28
00:00:35,220 --> 00:00:37,450
to the way things were before our fight.

29
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:42,210
Well, sometimes couples need a little time to recover.

30
00:00:42,210 --> 00:00:42,980
We won't.

31
00:00:43,370 --> 00:00:45,610
Carly asked for you to move out.

32
00:00:46,090 --> 00:00:47,680
You are moving out.

33
00:00:50,890 --> 00:00:53,510
How many kidneys do I need in my body to attend prom?

34
00:00:53,510 --> 00:00:54,370
Ryan...

35
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:56,190
Even if the surgery removes my kidney,

36
00:00:56,190 --> 00:00:57,620
it'll be laparoscopic,

37
00:00:57,620 --> 00:01:00,620
so my inpatient time will be seven days, tops.

38
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:02,380
And then three more days of rest at home.

39
00:01:02,810 --> 00:01:04,890
I can take my girlfriend to prom, right?

40
00:01:05,970 --> 00:01:07,750
That's not a purely medical decision.

41
00:01:07,750 --> 00:01:08,920
I have to draw some blood.

42
00:01:09,130 --> 00:01:11,000
What are the chances Dr. Melendez might be able

43
00:01:11,010 --> 00:01:13,160
to remove the tumor but spare Ryan's kidney?

44
00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:15,000
Well, the MRI will let us know

45
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,570
how much the chemo shrunk the tumor,

46
00:01:16,570 --> 00:01:18,240
but you shouldn't count on it.

47
00:01:18,930 --> 00:01:22,300
One chili burger, extra mustard, extra pickles.

48
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:24,020
Hi. Morning, Mr. Cooper.

49
00:01:24,140 --> 00:01:25,720
I'm not sure he can have that with his surgery...

50
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:27,990
Oh, he's fine until about 6:30 tonight.

51
00:01:28,810 --> 00:01:29,710
I know you.

52
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:32,610
Angie...Valens.

53
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:34,300
I helped put in your chemo port.

54
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,270
I owe you a big thank-you.

55
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:37,740
We met in chemo.

56
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:39,020
They should put us in a

57
00:01:39,020 --> 00:01:40,490
public service announcement or something.

58
00:01:40,490 --> 00:01:43,280
Yeah... "I lost a tumor and gained a boyfriend.

59
00:01:43,490 --> 00:01:44,300
Thanks, chemo."

60
00:01:48,610 --> 00:01:49,760
James McDougall?

61
00:01:49,770 --> 00:01:51,260
That's who we're here for, too.

62
00:01:51,310 --> 00:01:52,820
All of you can head over to Bay 4.

63
00:01:53,620 --> 00:01:55,940
Guy saw me six months ago for a stress fracture.

64
00:01:55,940 --> 00:01:57,880
He's a lunatic ultra-marathoner.

65
00:01:58,110 --> 00:01:59,790
I just hope he didn't go too hard too soon

66
00:01:59,790 --> 00:02:00,910
and break it again.

67
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:09,420
He didn't break it again.

70
00:02:24,070 --> 00:02:26,650
Your GP was right to start you on ketoprofen for the swelling,

71
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:28,250
but clearly, it isn't working.

72
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,700
That's why Drs. Murphy and Reznick

73
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:31,970
are going to block off some of your lymphatic channels.

74
00:02:31,970 --> 00:02:33,350
It should reduce production.

75
00:02:34,060 --> 00:02:36,070
The more pressing concern is why.

76
00:02:36,070 --> 00:02:38,650
Have you ever had surgery on your lymph nodes?

77
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,700
What about cancer or radiation treatment?

78
00:02:42,190 --> 00:02:44,220
No. Physically, I've always been healthy.

79
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,340
Physically?

80
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:46,000
I was diagnosed with

81
00:02:46,010 --> 00:02:48,630
Persistent Depressive Disorder when I was 16.

82
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:52,410
That's why you got to get me back out on the road, Doc.

83
00:02:52,650 --> 00:02:54,770
Are antidepressants not effective for you?

84
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,250
I mean, they help.

85
00:02:56,410 --> 00:02:58,740
But running really is key.

86
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:01,850
Saved my marriage and... my life.

87
00:03:01,910 --> 00:03:03,950
Lymphedema can be caused by an infection.

88
00:03:04,270 --> 00:03:06,250
He doesn't have a fever.

89
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:08,380
Ketoprofen can suppress fevers.

90
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:09,250
Let's get some cultures

91
00:03:09,250 --> 00:03:11,250
and start him on broad-spec antibiotics.

92
00:03:15,970 --> 00:03:19,400
As requested, your restock on enemas.

93
00:03:19,590 --> 00:03:20,550
Nice cover.

94
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:23,220
How've you been feeling?

95
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:25,210
The methotrexate is working great.

96
00:03:25,210 --> 00:03:27,320
No pain, no redness.

97
00:03:27,990 --> 00:03:29,610
Stiffness, flu-like symptoms?

98
00:03:29,610 --> 00:03:30,960
No. All good.

99
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:35,400
How long are you planning to hide out doing RA exams

100
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:37,170
and clipping diabetics' toenails?

101
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,490
Dizziness, headaches, nausea?

102
00:03:40,740 --> 00:03:43,480
I... Sometimes I'm a little queasy after I eat.

103
00:03:44,070 --> 00:03:46,630
You had to love neurosurgery.

104
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,510
How about we try to get you a medication

105
00:03:49,510 --> 00:03:51,060
that doesn't irritate your stomach?

106
00:03:51,060 --> 00:03:53,480
No. My hands feel great. That's all I care about.

107
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:56,020
You used to open up skulls

108
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:58,070
and poke around people's brains.

109
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:00,430
There's no way this fulfills you.

110
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,040
I enjoy it.

111
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:05,000
Or, rather, I usually enjoy it.

112
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:08,050
I'll let you get back to it.

113
00:04:10,730 --> 00:04:12,480
Maybe someone out there needs an enema.

114
00:04:17,790 --> 00:04:19,260
Got a measurement on the Wilms tumor?

115
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:20,900
Mm, not quite there yet.

116
00:04:21,950 --> 00:04:24,340
You mentioned 7 centimeters as our limit

117
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:25,790
to doing this laparoscopically.

118
00:04:25,790 --> 00:04:27,940
What if we pushed it to 7.2?

119
00:04:28,470 --> 00:04:29,870
Would speed up recovery.

120
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:31,630
By a few days.

121
00:04:33,420 --> 00:04:34,810
Forget I brought it up.

122
00:04:35,170 --> 00:04:37,340
Ryan wanting to take his girlfriend to prom

123
00:04:37,340 --> 00:04:40,010
should not factor into our surgical plan.

124
00:04:40,980 --> 00:04:42,030
Is he nuts about her?

125
00:04:42,030 --> 00:04:45,080
Ohh. Crazy, head over heels in love.

126
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:46,120
They both are.

127
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,460
Idiots.

128
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:51,760
I wouldn't mind being an idiot like that again.

129
00:04:52,990 --> 00:04:56,150
Though, I'm not sure I ever felt that way,

130
00:04:56,150 --> 00:04:57,440
totally happy.

131
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:59,160
So therapy's going well?

132
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:02,700
No metastasis in the lungs.

133
00:05:04,390 --> 00:05:05,200
Look at that.

134
00:05:11,450 --> 00:05:12,760
Your tumor is gone.

135
00:05:15,410 --> 00:05:16,050
Gone?

136
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,930
How's that possible?

137
00:05:19,010 --> 00:05:21,730
The chemotherapy worked better than we expected.

138
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:24,640
Wait, like, no tumor? Zero?

139
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,130
No need for surgery whatsoever?

140
00:05:26,130 --> 00:05:27,050
That is right.

141
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:28,870
These are discharge forms.

142
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,790
Both of my kidneys are taking you to prom!

143
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,510
Aah! Hell, yeah!

144
00:05:43,470 --> 00:05:44,250
Angie?

145
00:05:46,990 --> 00:05:48,800
- Angie! - She's having a seizure!

146
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:52,540
2 milligrams of lorazepam and portable oxygen, stat.

147
00:05:52,540 --> 00:05:53,770
Let's get that under her head.

148
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,230
His lungs are filled with fluid.

149
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:03,480
I need a chest X-ray and a bedside ultrasound.

150
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:05,050
And page Dr. Reznick.

151
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:20,110
Imaging has confirmed the reoccurrence

152
00:06:20,110 --> 00:06:21,020
of your brain tumor.

153
00:06:22,420 --> 00:06:23,400
What stage?

154
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:25,540
Three.

155
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,970
The best approach is surgery,

156
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:30,520
a wide resection of the tumor,

157
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:32,070
followed by radiation and chemo

158
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,560
to encourage full remission.

159
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:36,490
Sounds like a fun couple months.

160
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:41,100
Full recovery will probably take closer to eight.

161
00:06:46,150 --> 00:06:48,160
We can get through this, baby, just like last time.

162
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:52,460
W-when will the surgery be?

163
00:06:52,910 --> 00:06:54,860
We need to do some additional imaging,

164
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:56,560
and I'd like to consult a colleague

165
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,050
about the best surgical approach.

166
00:06:58,050 --> 00:06:59,100
That'll take a few days.

167
00:07:01,060 --> 00:07:02,130
Take your time.

168
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:05,090
Prom?

169
00:07:06,450 --> 00:07:07,200
Yeah.

170
00:07:07,350 --> 00:07:09,460
Now that Ryan can go, I have to go.

171
00:07:09,460 --> 00:07:10,380
Honey.

172
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:12,600
This is your health we're talking about.

173
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,610
Mom, please.

174
00:07:15,230 --> 00:07:18,230
I just want to do this one thing like a normal kid.

175
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,170
Can you tell her it's okay?

176
00:07:24,410 --> 00:07:25,240
We can't.

177
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,140
Until we remove your tumor,

178
00:07:26,140 --> 00:07:28,570
you're at risk of potentially fatal seizures.

179
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,320
After you're recovered,

180
00:07:32,330 --> 00:07:34,000
you and Ryan can get all dressed up,

181
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,370
and we'll go have dinner at the Grandview. Okay?

182
00:07:43,210 --> 00:07:44,270
Prom sucks.

183
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:46,630
My buddy had a fake ID.

184
00:07:46,630 --> 00:07:48,490
I got so drunk in the limo that I passed out

185
00:07:48,490 --> 00:07:50,160
and never made it into the dance.

186
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:53,260
Maybe that wasn't everybody's experience.

187
00:07:53,820 --> 00:07:55,750
I was prom king. My date was queen.

188
00:08:00,430 --> 00:08:01,780
I had the dress, I had the date,

189
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:03,640
I had the mom who got arrested.

190
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,910
Spent the night picking her up from the drunk tank.

191
00:08:05,910 --> 00:08:07,100
Did you see Park while you were there?

192
00:08:08,170 --> 00:08:10,910
Go to scheduling, get Angie's surgery set for Friday

193
00:08:10,910 --> 00:08:12,960
with the best neurosurgery OR nurses.

194
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:16,280
Let's go see Glassman.

195
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:18,590
Now I'm identifying

196
00:08:18,590 --> 00:08:20,470
the submillimeter lymphatic vessels.

197
00:08:20,470 --> 00:08:24,150
I need an 11-0 micro suture and a 70 micron needle.

198
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:27,090
Instead of harvesting nodes to this area,

199
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:30,190
could we redirect lymphatics away from his lymph system?

200
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:31,230
We could.

201
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:33,540
If you identify an appropriate vessel,

202
00:08:33,540 --> 00:08:34,870
you can make the connection.

203
00:08:35,230 --> 00:08:37,540
We're clearly not dealing with an infection.

204
00:08:37,590 --> 00:08:40,060
There must be a blockage somewhere in his lymph system.

205
00:08:40,060 --> 00:08:41,250
Most likely cancer.

206
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:45,140
His CBC didn't show any abnormal cells.

207
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:46,950
Lymphoma doesn't always show up.

208
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:49,880
We need to run cytology on his lymphatic fluid.

209
00:08:55,650 --> 00:08:57,900
It's either gonna be nasty or very nasty,

210
00:08:57,900 --> 00:08:59,280
depending upon how it attaches

211
00:08:59,290 --> 00:09:01,230
to the thalamus and fornix.

212
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:05,460
Which no imaging or testing can possibly determine.

213
00:09:06,610 --> 00:09:08,210
So, our options are?

214
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:11,660
Between an endoscopic approach or an open anterior one.

215
00:09:11,780 --> 00:09:13,150
That is correct.

216
00:09:15,540 --> 00:09:20,100
I'd run a stereotactic MRI with fiducials and DTI

217
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:22,900
to gauge how close the white matter tracts actually are.

218
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,520
You should scrub in.

219
00:09:26,990 --> 00:09:28,730
Another doctor can cover the clinic.

220
00:09:30,090 --> 00:09:33,190
I haven't been in an OR in over a year,

221
00:09:33,190 --> 00:09:34,770
and then, as a patient.

222
00:09:35,210 --> 00:09:36,970
I'm not asking you to cut.

223
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:39,280
But it'd be a huge value to have you there.

224
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:43,060
I appreciate that.

225
00:09:43,630 --> 00:09:44,650
I'll consider it.

226
00:09:59,170 --> 00:10:02,460
Hello. We need to run cytology on this lymphatic fluid.

227
00:10:02,460 --> 00:10:03,900
I would be happy to.

228
00:10:08,210 --> 00:10:09,730
Lea moved out this morning.

229
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,660
- Thank you. - You're welcome.

230
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:16,810
Can you come over tonight?

231
00:10:16,810 --> 00:10:18,520
Uh, that probably won't work...

232
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:20,150
Or we could go to your apartment?

233
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:22,710
I can't.

234
00:10:25,060 --> 00:10:27,280
Lea said that it might take time

235
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:29,430
for us to recover from our fight.

236
00:10:29,430 --> 00:10:31,330
But I told her that we were okay.

237
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:32,480
We are.

238
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:35,070
I made plans tonight.

239
00:10:35,090 --> 00:10:37,730
To hang out with a friend who just got fired.

240
00:10:38,490 --> 00:10:41,060
But I would love to come over tomorrow night.

241
00:10:41,740 --> 00:10:42,540
Okay.

242
00:10:43,430 --> 00:10:45,420
I'll put a rush on this test, too.

243
00:10:53,510 --> 00:10:56,180
Your lymphovenous anastomosis technique...

244
00:10:56,180 --> 00:10:57,070
I was impressed.

245
00:10:58,180 --> 00:10:59,480
It's a little early in the morning

246
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:00,920
to be sucking up, Reznick.

247
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:02,820
Not for me. I like to get a jump on things.

248
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:05,350
I'm fascinated by the way you use plastic procedures,

249
00:11:05,350 --> 00:11:08,140
like microsurgery, in other surgical specialties.

250
00:11:08,140 --> 00:11:10,480
I thought it might make an interesting topic for a paper.

251
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:12,590
Want to write it with me?

252
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:14,970
Yes.

253
00:11:15,190 --> 00:11:16,080
Let's talk and eat.

254
00:11:19,610 --> 00:11:20,920
That's not breakfast.

255
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:23,720
I'm buying.

256
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,750
What publications do you want to target?

257
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:30,920
Last time, Angie had bad post-op vomiting.

258
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:32,420
- Of course. I'll make note of it... - Excuse me.

259
00:11:34,290 --> 00:11:37,090
She's asleep. She needs her rest.

260
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:38,800
I'll wait out here until she's awake.

261
00:11:38,940 --> 00:11:40,750
Ryan, your immune system is weak.

262
00:11:40,750 --> 00:11:41,690
It would be so easy for

263
00:11:41,690 --> 00:11:43,760
you to pick up a bug and pass it to Angie.

264
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:46,040
I haven't been around anyone but my dad. I swear.

265
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:47,320
He could wear a mask.

266
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:54,660
After Angie's surgery, we'll see about arranging a visit.

267
00:11:54,810 --> 00:11:56,220
Please tell her Ryan came by.

268
00:11:59,910 --> 00:12:01,890
I'm sorry if I overstepped.

269
00:12:02,650 --> 00:12:04,040
I'd like to change Angie's status

270
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:05,680
to "No visitors" on her chart.

271
00:12:05,940 --> 00:12:06,690
Yeah.

272
00:12:14,450 --> 00:12:15,760
Please take Mr. McDougall to his room.

273
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:16,860
I'll be there in a moment.

274
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:20,870
Is that James McDougall?

275
00:12:21,770 --> 00:12:23,550
- And the woman with him? - His wife.

276
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:24,930
Is it cancer? 

277
00:12:26,020 --> 00:12:27,260
No... Worse.

278
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:30,720
His lymphedema is caused by a genetic mutation.

279
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:33,800
If you don't find a medication he responds to,

280
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:35,800
he'll drown from the inside.

281
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:41,540
The mutation is on James' ARAF gene.

282
00:12:41,540 --> 00:12:43,270
It makes an enzyme called kinase,

283
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:45,650
which can cause cells to overproliferate.

284
00:12:45,650 --> 00:12:47,090
It's a genetic condition.

285
00:12:48,930 --> 00:12:50,370
What set it off now?

286
00:12:50,370 --> 00:12:51,760
Probably the stress fracture.

287
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:53,360
Sent his immune system into overdrive,

288
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:55,040
which fired up his lymphatic system.

289
00:12:55,810 --> 00:12:57,850
What treatment protocol targets this mutation?

290
00:12:57,900 --> 00:12:59,640
An MEK inhibitor.

291
00:12:59,650 --> 00:13:00,950
The problem is, which one?

292
00:13:00,950 --> 00:13:02,430
There are 41 possibilities,

293
00:13:02,430 --> 00:13:04,300
each with different side effects.

