Septal vein... There's your bleeder.

567
00:32:15,250 --> 00:32:16,480
Cauterize away.

568
00:33:01,710 --> 00:33:02,860
Micro dissector.

569
00:33:08,340 --> 00:33:09,450
The tumor's immobile.

570
00:33:09,970 --> 00:33:12,090
I can't resect it without injuring the nerve tracts.

571
00:33:12,090 --> 00:33:13,490
She'd be comatose.

572
00:33:13,930 --> 00:33:15,460
Try sharp dissection.

573
00:33:17,020 --> 00:33:18,430
- I can't get a plane. -How bad?

574
00:33:18,430 --> 00:33:20,460
It's completely invaded her thalamus.

575
00:33:20,730 --> 00:33:24,210
Thin it out with a suction aspirator.

576
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:31,260
It's too adherent.

577
00:33:31,740 --> 00:33:33,350
If I keep going, I'm gonna kill her.

578
00:33:35,700 --> 00:33:36,640
Any ideas?

579
00:33:58,850 --> 00:34:02,380
Tell ICU Angie will be coming sooner than we planned.

580
00:34:04,100 --> 00:34:05,090
Let's close her up.

581
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:24,070
What next?

582
00:34:24,540 --> 00:34:26,730
Another round of radiation, chemo?

583
00:34:29,670 --> 00:34:32,340
Her carcinoma is

584
00:34:32,340 --> 00:34:35,450
unlikely to respond to those therapies.

585
00:34:38,970 --> 00:34:41,290
No. We have to try.

586
00:34:42,140 --> 00:34:43,710
Angie will want to fight.

587
00:34:43,890 --> 00:34:44,640
She's seizing.

588
00:34:44,640 --> 00:34:46,150
Give me lorazepam and Dilantin, stat.

589
00:34:46,150 --> 00:34:47,760
Phenobarb and propofol on deck.

590
00:35:10,380 --> 00:35:11,320
You're crying.

591
00:35:15,130 --> 00:35:16,030
Yes.

592
00:35:19,930 --> 00:35:20,830
Why?

593
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:25,840
I found James on Facebook.

594
00:35:27,810 --> 00:35:30,380
He and Marjorie want to go to Costa Rica.

595
00:35:32,190 --> 00:35:35,680
Their dog is a three-legged rescue named Tripod.

596
00:35:40,450 --> 00:35:42,730
He's not a slide. He's a person.

597
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:45,440
He's a good person.

598
00:35:45,620 --> 00:35:46,810
And he might die.

599
00:35:48,830 --> 00:35:51,240
This is why I like to stay in the lab.

600
00:35:56,590 --> 00:35:57,580
That...

601
00:35:58,720 --> 00:36:01,290
Is a very dumb thing to say.

602
00:36:04,020 --> 00:36:06,130
If you had stayed in the lab,

603
00:36:06,850 --> 00:36:09,960
James would probably be dead already.

604
00:36:12,690 --> 00:36:17,720
Your plan with the zebrafish gave him a chance.

605
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:22,730
It was a beautiful, perfect idea,

606
00:36:23,830 --> 00:36:26,770
from a beautiful, almost perfect person.

607
00:36:32,670 --> 00:36:35,150
Your earlobes are lopsided.

608
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:10,190
I'm so sorry.

609
00:37:11,370 --> 00:37:12,690
We couldn't save her.

610
00:37:33,730 --> 00:37:34,630
Ms. Valens?

611
00:38:07,810 --> 00:38:09,420
Nice call on the zebrafish.

612
00:38:28,990 --> 00:38:31,290
About our paper, let's meet weekly.

613
00:38:31,290 --> 00:38:34,040
I'm thinking lunch every Tuesday in the cafeteria.

614
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:34,940
Perfect.

615
00:38:45,550 --> 00:38:48,290
I heard about Melendez's patient.

616
00:38:51,470 --> 00:38:52,330
Yeah.

617
00:39:02,690 --> 00:39:04,050
You were right.

618
00:39:04,110 --> 00:39:08,560
I should probably try another medication for my RA.

619
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:11,690
I need solid food.

620
00:39:23,510 --> 00:39:25,280
Claire? Wait up.

621
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:27,620
You okay?

622
00:39:28,260 --> 00:39:30,080
Fine. I'm just tired.

623
00:39:32,350 --> 00:39:34,430
You did an amazing thing for Angie.

624
00:39:34,430 --> 00:39:36,880
You gave her mother a memory that she will have forever.

625
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:39,630
Well, it won't make up for the daughter she lost.

626
00:39:40,310 --> 00:39:41,220
You're angry.

627
00:39:41,570 --> 00:39:43,730
I'm not. I am sad.

628
00:39:43,740 --> 00:39:45,690
- Who are you angry at? - I'm not.

629
00:39:45,700 --> 00:39:46,950
Are you angry at me and Glassman

630
00:39:46,950 --> 00:39:47,950
because we couldn't save her?

631
00:39:47,950 --> 00:39:49,660
- No! - At Angie?

632
00:39:49,660 --> 00:39:52,140
No, you can't be mad at someone for dying!

633
00:39:53,580 --> 00:39:55,310
That's not true. You know that.

634
00:39:57,790 --> 00:39:59,360
She was sick.

635
00:39:59,540 --> 00:40:01,320
And she was trying to get better.

636
00:40:01,750 --> 00:40:03,610
She failed and left you alone,

637
00:40:04,050 --> 00:40:06,530
after you'd spent a lifetime trying to take care of her.

638
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:09,830
You have every reason to be mad at your mother.

639
00:40:11,350 --> 00:40:12,830
I hate feeling this way.

640
00:40:13,100 --> 00:40:15,020
My whole life, I've been angry at her,

641
00:40:15,020 --> 00:40:16,920
and now it will never change.

642
00:40:18,140 --> 00:40:19,800
I don't know how to stop.

643
00:40:23,650 --> 00:40:25,220
Therapy will help.

644
00:40:26,190 --> 00:40:27,340
Time will help.

645
00:40:29,660 --> 00:40:32,140
There is one other thing that's worked for me.

646
00:40:44,500 --> 00:40:46,820
Did we fix our mutation?

647
00:41:00,270 --> 00:41:01,590
That the best you got?

